<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Home Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.4/css/all.min.css"> 
    <style>
        .card {
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
            transition: 0.3s;
            width: 400px; 
            height: auto; 
            margin: 40px; 
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            text-align: center;
            overflow: hidden; 
            margin-bottom: 40px; 
            cursor: pointer; 
        }

            .card:hover {
                box-shadow: 0 8px 16px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
            }

        .container {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            margin-top: 50px; 
        }

        .card-title {
            font-size: 40px; 
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-top: 10px; 
            margin-bottom: 10px; 
            white-space: nowrap; 
            overflow: hidden; 
            text-overflow: ellipsis; 
        }

        .description {
            font-size: 18px; 
            margin-top: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 20px; 
            overflow: hidden; 
            text-overflow: ellipsis; 
        }

        .star-icon {
            color: #FFD700; 
            font-size: 36px; 
            margin-bottom: 10px; 
        }

        .second-line {
            font-size: 20px; 
            color: #666; 
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="card" id="T1518Card">
            <i class="fas fa-star star-icon"></i>
            <h2 class="card-title">T1518</h2>
            <p class="second-line">Software Discovery</p>
            <p class="description">The T1518 attack tries to obtain the list of software and their versions installed on the system or cloud environment and tests this vulnerability. Using the information they gain from Software Discovery during automated discovery, attackers can shape their subsequent behavior, such as whether to fully infect the target or attempt certain actions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card" id="T1614Card">
            <i class="fas fa-star star-icon"></i> 
            <h2 class="card-title">T1614</h2>
            <p class="second-line">System Location Discovery</p>
            <p class="description">The T1614 attack collects information to calculate the victim's location and tests this vulnerability. Using the information they obtain from System Location Discovery during automated discovery, attackers can shape their subsequent behavior, such as whether to fully infect the target or attempt certain actions.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        const T1518Card = document.getElementById('T1518Card');
        const T1614Card = document.getElementById('T1614Card');

        T1518Card.addEventListener('click', function () {
            window.location.href = 'https://localhost:44382/Attack/T1518'; 
        });

        T1614Card.addEventListener('click', function () {
            window.location.href = 'https://localhost:44382/Attack/T1614'; 
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
